  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "uboot-tools security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for uboot-tools is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This package includes the mkimage program, which allows generation of U-Boot images in various formats, and the fw_printenv and fw_setenv programs to read and modify U-Boot\u0026apos;s environment.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn integer overflow in ext4fs_read_symlink in Das U-Boot before 2025.01-rc1 occurs for zalloc (adding one to an le32 variable) via a crafted ext4 filesystem with an inode size of 0xffffffff, resulting in a malloc of zero and resultant memory overwrite.(CVE-2024-57256)\n\nInteger overflows in memory allocation in Das U-Boot before 2025.01-rc1 occur for a crafted squashfs filesystem via sbrk, via request2size, or because ptrdiff_t is mishandled on x86_64.(CVE-2024-57258)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for uboot-tools is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "uboot-tools",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
